\label{P.Perfect}
	For $m\geq 2$ let $\fC_m$ be the class of all perfect groups $G$ of commutator width $\leq  m$ that satisfy the following condition. 
	\begin{itemize}
		\item [($\dagger$)] If $H\trianglelefteq G$ is nonabelian, then $C_G(H)=Z(G)$. 
	\end{itemize}
	Then $\fC_m$ recognizes coordinates.

\label{L.perfect}
	Suppose that $G$ is a perfect group of commutator width $\leq  m$ that satisfies condition  ($\dagger$). Then for all $a$ and $b$ in $G$ the following condition holds if and only if $a= e \rightarrow b=e$ holds. 		
	\begin{enumerate}
		\item [(*)] For all $z_i, t_i$, $i\leq m$,  such that $a=\prod_{i\leq m} [z_i,t_i]$ there are $x_i,y_i$, $i\leq m$ such that   $b=\prod_i [x_i,y_i]$, and such that we have 
		\[
